# .gitignore for prawl.fft.offensivechemist
#
# Self-contained: this repo does NOT rely on ~/.gitignore_global. Every rule the
# project needs lives here so a fresh clone on any machine ignores the right things.

# --- Python (tools/ scripts) ---
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# --- SQLite caches (decode/reference DBs; never source) ---
*.sqlite

# --- Load-bearing build inputs that are NOT committed ---
# working/ = the pristine vanilla decode caches (item.en.sqlite + ability.en.nxd)
# that patch_names.py / patch_ability_names.py diff their output against, plus the
# nxd/icon scratch dirs those scripts write. See README "Pristine caches".
working/

# --- Release / packaging artifacts ---
Publish/
dist/
*.zip

# --- OS / editor cruft ---
*.tmp
*.temp
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vs/
.vscode/
*.user

# NOTE: mod/FFTIVC/ (generated tables + nxd + icons) IS committed -- the nxd build
# is a manual FF16Tools step, so we preserve the built artifacts in the tree.

# A case-insensitive "Icon" rule (from some global/OS ignore files) would ignore
# our whole ui/ffto/icon/ tree on a case-insensitive filesystem. Re-include it:
!mod/FFTIVC/data/enhanced/ui/ffto/icon/
!mod/FFTIVC/data/enhanced/ui/ffto/icon/**
